<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>	<item><status>past</status><description>&lt;p&gt;Our second of three meeting on C. S. Peirce will look at the writings of his third system where he develops his Doubt-Belief theory and influential Pragmatist theory of meaning. &lt;br /&gt;

 &lt;br /&gt;

Below is a list of the third system readings and links to where they can be found online. For those interested in reading in the traditional book format I would recommend The Essential Peirce-Selected Philosophical Writings Vol. 1 &amp;amp; 2 edited by the Peirce Edition Project and published by Indiana University Press. &lt;br /&gt;

